The '''March for Life Chicago''' is an annual gathering of [[anti-abortion movement|pro-life]] people and organizations from the Midwest in the city of [[Chicago]]. It occurs typically the weekend prior to or close to the anniversary of [[Roe vs. Wade]], January 22. This event is held as a Midwest version of the [[March for Life (Washington, D.C.)|March for Life]] in Washington, DC.<ref>{{cite news|title=Chicago Tribune|url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2014-01-19/news/chi-chicago-abortion-rally-20140119_1_abortion-foes-abortion-opponents-legalized-abortion}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Archdiocese Release|url=http://www.archchicago.org/news_releases/news_2014/news_140116.html}}</ref>
== Organizers == The March for Life Chicago is organized by a coalition of pro-life organizations in the Chicago area. These include: * Aid for Women * Archdiocese of Chicago * Catholic Conference of Illinois * Couples for Christ Foundation for Family and Life * Knights of Columbus * Illinois Right to Life * Lake County Right to Life * Orthodox Church of America * Pro-Life Action League * Relevant Radio * [[Students for Life of Illinois]] * Thomas More Society
